1) Make sure saslauthd is running.
2) Create file /etc/sasl2/sample.conf
pwcheck_method: saslauthd
mech_list: plain login
3) Run server: cyrus_sasl_sample_server -p 2670 -s login
This will use the PAM's "login" configuration
4) Run client: cyrus_sasl_sample_client -p 2670 localhost


Another
1) Remove /etc/sasl2/sample.conf
2) sudo saslpasswd2 rich
   ... enter password
3) sudo cyrus_sasl_sample_server -p 2670
4) cyrus_sasl_sample_client -p 2670 localhost
